Phylosophy:
    1. Changes should be atomic. Check all things before changing anything.


# Local functions.
_setprev - mark a task ID as previous
_setcurr - mark a task ID as current


# Public functions
getprev     - get previous task ID
getcurr     - get current task ID
exist       - check that ID exists in database
add         - add new task ID into the database
del         - delete task ID  from the database
swap        - swap current and previous task IDs
move        - move task ID to new status
list        - list task IDs

# Delete 'em. Use move() instead.
setcurr     - set task ID as current
unsetcurr   - unset task ID (move its status to ACTV)

get(id)
set(id, status)
